        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1978-06-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1978-06-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="25"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d25">
                <head>25. Memorandum From the President’s Assistant for National Security Affairs
                    (Brzezinski) to President <persName corresp="#p_CJE_1">Carter</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d25fn1">Source: Carter Library, Brzezinski
                        Donated Material, Subject File, Box 41, Weekly Report (to the President),
                        61–71: (6/78–9/78). Secret. <persName corresp="#p_CJE_1">Carter</persName>
                        initialed the top of the memorandum.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1978-06-23">June 23, 1978</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss> Weekly Report #64</item>
                </list>
                <p>[Omitted here is information unrelated to Indochina.]</p>
                <p rend="sectiontitleital">3. Alerts</p>
                <p rend="sectiontitleital">Vietnamese Initiative</p>
                <p>As Cy noted in his evening report recently,<note n="2" xml:id="d25fn2">Not
                        further identified.</note> the Vietnamese are signalling an interest in
                    advancing rapidly their relations with us. They will be sending a group of
                    experts to visit our <gloss target="#t_MIA_1">MIA</gloss> Identification
                    Laboratory in Hawaii during the week of July 5–10. They have also hinted at a
                    desire to renew contact with <persName corresp="#p_HRC_1">Dick
                        Holbrooke</persName> to resume discussions on normalization. They will seek
                    to involve you directly or indirectly in Congressman <persName
                        corresp="#p_MGS_1">Montgomery</persName>’s likely visit to Hanoi in late
                    fall. While accepting the <gloss target="#t_MIA_1">MIA</gloss> visit, we should
                    restrain ourselves from responding to Vietnamese initiatives for two reasons:
                    (1) the domestic political reaction would be quite negative; (2) given current
                        <pb facs="0120" n="91" xml:id="pg_91"/> Chinese-Vietnamese animosities,
                    efforts to improve relations with Vietnam, which would strengthen Hanoi’s
                    international position, could adversely affect our efforts to elicit some
                    flexibility from Peking.<note n="3" xml:id="d25fn3">
                        <persName corresp="#p_CJE_1">Carter</persName> wrote in the left-hand margin
                        adjacent to this paragraph, “Do <hi rend="italic">not</hi> send a negative
                        signal. Just delay.”</note>
                </p>
                <p>[Omitted here is information unrelated to Indochina.]</p>
            </div>
